  "citation": "Goldberg, L.R. (1992). Psychological Assessment, 4, 26-42.",
  "response_scale": "1=Very Inaccurate  2=Moderately Inaccurate  3=Neither  4=Moderately Accurate  5=Very Accurate",
  "scoring_rule": "+keyed: scored_value = raw(1-5).  -keyed: scored_value = 6-raw.  Factor score = sum of 10 scored_values (range 10-50).",
  "factors": {
    "Extraversion": {
      "n_items": 10,
      "alpha": 0.87,
      "mbti_proxy": "EI – high=E, low=I"
    },
    "Agreeableness": {
      "n_items": 10,
      "alpha": 0.82,
      "mbti_proxy": "TF – high=F, low=T (INVERTED: high agree = Feeling)"
    },
    "Conscientiousness": {
      "n_items": 10,
      "alpha": 0.79,
      "mbti_proxy": "JP – high=J, low=P"
    },
    "Emotional Stability": {
      "n_items": 10,
      "alpha": 0.86,
      "mbti_proxy": "None – inverse of Neuroticism; no MBTI counterpart"
    },
    "Intellect/Openness": {
      "n_items": 10,
      "alpha": 0.84,
      "mbti_proxy": "NS – high=N, low=S"
    }
  },
  "notes": [
    "The same source page also publishes 20-item versions of each factor (alpha .88-.91). The 50-item set uses the 10-item versions.",
    "MBTI proxy mappings are researcher-constructed; Agreeableness maps INVERSELY to TF (high=F, low=T).",
    "Emotional Stability (Factor IV) has no MBTI counterpart — it is the inverse of NEO Neuroticism.",
    "Item E3 ('Start conversations') appears only in the 20-item Extraversion scale; included here as a core marker.",
    "For Bayesian adaptive MBTI use: recommend weighting items by their factor loading magnitude, not uniformly."
  ],
